====Usage notes====
* ''This note is discussed on the talk page.''
* Beginning in the 1950s, the term '''communism''' was used to describe something negative. This usage is very similar to the way that the word ''[[gay]]'' is used. This practice is derived from the fact that people, during the [[Wikipedia:Red Scare|Red Scare]], accused those they disliked of being communists, often for absurd or impossible reasons. For example, one might describe a difficult test as "communism". This colloquial usage is restricted primarily to [[American English]]. See ''[[Communism]]''.

